1. git status (The Radar)
    Check what has changed before doing anything else.
    Function: Lists files that have been modified, created, or deleted but not yet prepared for upload.

2. git add (The Staging Area)
    Move your changes from the working directory to the "Staging Area" (like putting a letter in an envelope).
    Function: Selects which changes will be included in the next snapshot.
    git add . - Add all
    git add file_name - adds a specific file

3. git commit (Saving Local History)
    "Seal the envelope." This saves the version on your computer.
    Function: Creates a permanent snapshot of the project at this moment.
    Flag -m: Allows you to type the description message directly.

4. git push (Upload to GitHub)
    Send your local commits to the cloud.
    Function: Synchronizes your local history with the remote server.